b'<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>\n\n\n<!DOCTYPE workbook_page PUBLIC " -//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Workbook Page MathML 3.8//EN" "http://oli.web.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_workbook_page_mathml_3_8.dtd">\n<workbook_page id="p7b_balance_redox_basic" xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/"\n    xmlns:bib="http://bibtexml.sf.net/" xmlns:pref="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/preferences/"\n    xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:theme="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/presentation/"\n    xmlns:wb="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/activity/workbook/">\n\n\n    <head>\n        <title>Balancing Redox Equations in Basic Solutions</title>\n        <objref idref="balance_redox"/>\n\n    </head>\n\n    <body>\n\n        <p>Recall that basic solutions have excess hydroxide ions. Some of these hydroxide ions will\n            react with hydrogen ions to produce water. The simplest way to generate the balanced\n            overall equation in basic solution is to start with the balanced equation in acidic\n            solution, then \xe2\x80\x9cconvert\xe2\x80\x9d it to the equation for basic solution.</p>\n       \n        <image src="../../../webcontent/green_line.png"></image>\n        <dl>\n            <dt>Steps for Balancing Oxidation-Reduction Reactions in Basic Solution</dt>\n            <dd>\n                <p><em>Follow the steps for balancing in acidic solution.</em></p>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Write unbalanced half-reactions.</li>\n                    <li>Balance each half reaction: <ul>\n                            <li>First balance the elements (except for H and O).</li>\n                            <li>Balance O then H with H<sub>2</sub>O and H<sup>+</sup>\n                                respectively.</li>\n                            <li>Then balance charge by adding electrons.</li>\n                        </ul>\n                    </li>\n                    <li>Make the electrons gained and lost equal by multiplying the half-reactions\n                        by the appropriate factor.</li>\n                    <li>Add the balanced half-reactions together.</li>\n                </ul>\n                <p><em>Additional Step for Balancing in Basic Solution</em></p>\n                <ul>\n                    <li>Eliminate H<sup>+</sup> by adding OH<sup>-</sup> and forming water. You must\n                        add the same number of OH<sup>-</sup> to each side of the equation.</li>\n                    <li>Check the overall reaction to make sure the mass and charge are\n                        balanced.</li>\n                </ul>\n            </dd>\n        </dl>\n        <image src="../../../webcontent/green_line.png"></image>\n\n        <example>\n            <p>Balance the following equation in basic solution.</p>\n            <formula>$$\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_4^-(aq)\\;\\;\\longrightarrow\\;\\;{\\mathrm{ClO}}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)$$</formula>\n\n            <p> First following the same steps as we did in acidic solution.</p>\n\n\n\n            <ul>\n                <li><em>Write unbalanced half-reactions.</em></li>\n            </ul>\n            <formula>$$\\begin{array}{l}\\mathrm{oxidation}:\\;\\;\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\;{\\mathrm{ClO}}_3^-(aq)\\\\\\mathrm{reduction}:\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_4^-(aq)\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\end{array}$$</formula>\n            <ul>\n                <li><em>Balance each half reaction:</em>\n                </li>\n\n            </ul>\n            <formula>$$\\begin{array}{l}3\\;{\\mathrm H}_2\\mathrm\n                O(l)\\;+\\;\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\;{\\mathrm{ClO}}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;6\\;\\mathrm\n                H^+(aq)\\;+\\;6\\;\\mathrm e^-\\\\3\\;\\mathrm e^-\\;+\\;4\\;\\mathrm\n                H^+(aq)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_4^-(aq)\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm O(l)\\;\\end{array}$$</formula>\n            <ul>\n                <li><em>Make the electrons gained and lost equal by multiplying the half-reactions\n                        by the appropriate factor.</em></li>\n            </ul>\n            <ul>\n                <li><em>Add the balanced half-reactions together.</em></li>\n            </ul>\n            <formula>$$\\begin{array}{l}\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;\\;3\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm\n                O(l)\\;+\\;\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\;{\\mathrm{ClO}}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;6\\;\\mathrm\n                H^+(aq)\\;+\\;6\\;\\mathrm e^-\\\\\\underline{6\\;\\mathrm e^-\\;+\\;8\\;\\mathrm\n                H^+(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_4^-(aq)\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\;+\\;4\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm\n                O(l)\\;(\\mathrm{multiplied}\\;\\mathrm{by}\\;2)}\\\\\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_4^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm\n                H^+(aq)\\;\\rightarrow\\;{\\mathrm{ClO}}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm O(l)\\end{array}$$</formula>\n\n            <p><em>Additional Step for Balancing in Basic Solution</em></p>\n            <ul>\n                <li><em>Eliminate H<sup>+</sup> by adding OH<sup>-</sup> and forming water. You must\n                        add the same number of OH<sup>-</sup> to each side of the\n                    equation.</em></li>\n            </ul>\n            <formula>$$\\begin{array}{l}\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm{MnO}_4^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm\n                H^+(aq)\\;+\\;\\boxed{2\\;\\mathrm{OH}^-(\\mathrm{aq})}\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\mathrm{ClO}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm\n                O(l)\\;+\\;\\boxed{2\\;\\mathrm{OH}^-(\\mathrm{aq})}\\\\\\mathrm{yields}:\\\\\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm{MnO}_4^-(aq)\\;+\\boxed{\\;2\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm O(\\mathrm\n                l)\\;}\\rightarrow\\;\\mathrm{ClO}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\;+\\boxed{\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2\\mathrm O(\\mathrm\n                l)}\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm{OH}^-(aq)\\\\\\mathrm{one}\\;\\mathrm{water}\\;\\mathrm{molecule}\\;\\mathrm{cancels}\\;\\mathrm{to}\\;\\mathrm{yield}:\\end{array}$$</formula>\n            <formula>$$\\mathrm{Cl}^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm{MnO}_4^-(aq)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm H}_2\\mathrm\n                O(l)\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\mathrm{ClO}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;2\\;{\\mathrm{MnO}}_2(s)\\;+\\;2\\;\\mathrm{OH}^-(aq)$$</formula>\n            <ul>\n                <li><em>Check the overall reaction to make sure the mass and charge are\n                        balanced</em>.</li>\n            </ul>\n            <formula>$$\\begin{array}{l}\\mathrm{Cl}:\\;(1\\times1\\;)\\;=\\;(1\\times1)\\;-\\;\\mathrm{balanced}\\\\\\mathrm{Mn}:\\;(2\\times1)\\;=\\;(2\\times1)\\;-\\;\\mathrm{balanced}\\\\\\mathrm\n                H:\\;(1\\times2)\\;=\\;(2\\times1)\\;-\\;\\mathrm{balanced}\\\\\\mathrm\n                O:\\;(2\\times4+1\\times1)\\;=\\;(3\\times1+2\\times2+2\\times1)\\;-\\;\\mathrm{balanced}\\\\\\mathrm{Charge}:\\;\\lbrack1\\times(-1)+2\\times(-1)\\rbrack\\;=\\;\\lbrack1\\times(-1)+2\\times(-1)\\rbrack\\;-\\;\\mathrm{balanced}\\end{array}$$</formula>\n\n        </example>\n        <composite_activity purpose="learnbydoing">\n            <formula>$$\\mathrm{Al}\\;+\\;{\\mathrm{CrO}}_4^{2-}\\;\\;\\rightarrow\\;\\;\\mathrm{Al}(\\mathrm{OH})_3\\;+\\;\\mathrm{Cr}(\\mathrm{OH})_4^-$$</formula>\n            <wb:inline idref="balance_basic_lbd"/>\n        </composite_activity>\n\n        <composite_activity purpose="didigetthis">\n            <p>On a separate sheet of paper, balance the equation below in basic solution. Answer\n                the following questions about the <em>final overall equation</em>.</p>\n            <formula>$${\\mathrm{NO}}_3^-(aq)\\;+\\;{\\mathrm\n                H}_2(g)\\;\\longrightarrow\\;\\mathrm{NO}(g)$$</formula>\n            <wb:inline idref="balance_basic_digt"/>\n        </composite_activity>\n\n        <p>Adapted from <link href="https://cnx.org/contents/havxkyvS@9.422:b39avmGq@29/Preface"\n                >Openstax Chemistry</link> under <link\n                href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/"> Creative Commons Attribution\n                4.0 License. </link></p>\n        <p>Download for free at <link\n                href="http://cnx.org/contents/85abf193-2bd2-4908-8563-90b8a7ac8df6@9.312"\n                >http://cnx.org/contents/85abf193-2bd2-4908-8563-90b8a7ac8df6@9.312.</link></p>\n\n    </body>\n</workbook_page>\n'